"American here. I am not pro China. I respect and dislike both countries for various reasons, and understand animosity is bread from competition over the number one economy. It's human nature. Just as nature is communicating to us that human population growth has been too fast on Earth.

Apologies for the convoluted message. God Bless all of us, we will need that level of intervention."

snippet.textDisplay: Just my opinion here folks. But with all due respect to all of these so-called "experts", I'll error on the side of caution and wear my PPE regardless if they feel it's needed or not. While there is even a small chance that I may breathe this bug into my system I will wear my mask. if someone has to, for one reason or another,  be out in public their PPE is a good barrier from this bug. Masks work by keeping sick people from spreading the disease and they also help by keeping others from breathing it in.  We have to consider that even with all of the CDC warnings/instructions to sick people not every sick person will be responsible enough to isolate themselves/wear a mask.
